<L>__{interior dalai lama's private rooms, the potala day}
<A>__{the prime ministers, lukhangwa and lobsang tashi, submit their resignations to his holiness. the boy takes the roll of parchment from them.}
<C>__{tenzin gyatso}
<D>__{i am so sorry.}
<C>__{lukhangwa}
<D>__{it must be done. we can no longer meet with the chinese, they refuse us.}
<A>__{we hear the sounds of those chinese tubas and trumpets. we hear trucks.}
<C>__{tenzin gyatso}
<D>__{i accept your resignations.}
<C>__{lobsang tashi}
<D>__{have you chosen your new prime ministers, holiness?}
<C>__{tenzin gyatso}
<D>__{there will be no new prime ministers.}
<C>__{lukhangwa}
<D>__{you will face great difficulties, holiness.}
<A>__{the boy affixes his small piece of parchment to the document and makes a mark on it.}
<C>__{tenzin gyatso}
<D>__{they have taken away our silence.}
